<!-- vraag_01 -->
    <div id="vraag_01" style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(29000px, -1500px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(1); transform-style: preserve-3d; "  class="step slide past" data-x="29000" data-y="-1500">

     <div style="width: 90%;  position: absolute; top: 20px; text-align:center;"><p style="font-size:200%;">Vraag 1</p><p style="font-size:100%; position:relative; top:20px;"></p></div>

<div style="position: absolute; top: 200px; left:100px; text-align:left; font-size:100%;">

<p>Which command will set the local machine's timezone to UTC?</p><br>
<ul>
<li style="list-style:disc;">cat UTC > /etc/timezone</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">ln -s /usr/share/zoneinfo/UTC /etc/localtime</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">date -timezone=UTC</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">mv /usr/timezone/UTC /etc</li>
</ul>


</div>

	<div id="container" style="position: absolute; bottom: 0; font-size:40%;">
  		<div id="left"><a href="http://www.linuxamsterdam.nl" target="_blank"><img src="la.svg" width=204px height=68px></a></div>
  		<div id="right"><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank"><img src="cc_by-sa.svg" width=88px height=31px></a></div>
  		<div id="center">LPIC-1 | Section 107.3 | Page 31/32</div>  

	</div>
</div>

<!-- vraag_02 -->
    <div id="vraag_02" style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(30000px, -1500px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(1); transform-style: preserve-3d; "  class="step slide past" data-x="30000" data-y="-1500">

     <div style="width: 90%;  position: absolute; top: 20px; text-align:center;"><p style="font-size:200%;">Vraag 2</p><p style="font-size:100%; position:relative; top:20px;"></p></div>

<div style="position: absolute; top: 200px; left:100px; text-align:left; font-size:100%;">

<p>With which command you can convert a file to a different encoding. (Convert characters in input file to another)</p><br>
